obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (33111)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33111&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Sales Tax`
  line `Act, 1975.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Administrator may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st October, 1975, vide Delhi Administrator notification No. F. 4-61-1975- F in (General) (i), dated 10th October, 1975,`
  line `Published in Delhi, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, dated 10th October, 1975, Part IV.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (33112)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33112&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of Delhi appointed by the President under`
  line `article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) "business" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any trade, commerce or manufacture or any adventure or concern in the nature of trade,`
  line `commerce or manufacture whether or not such trade, commerce, manufacture, adventure or`
  line `concern is carried on with a motive to make gain or profit and whether or not any gain or profit`
  line `accrues from such trade, commerce, manufacture, adventure or concern; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any transaction in connection with, or incidental or ancillary to, such trade, commerce,`
  line `manufacture, adventure or concern;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Sales Tax appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) "dealer" means any person who carries on business of selling goods in Delhi and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government or a State Government carrying on such business;`
  line
  line `(ii) an incorporated society (including a co-operative society), club or association which sells`
  line `or supplies goods, whether or not in the course of business, to its members for cash or for`
  line `deferred payment or for commission, remuneration or other valuable consideration;`
  line
  line `(iii) a manager, factor, broker, commission agent, del credere agent, or any mercantile agent,`
  line `by whatever name called, and whether of the same description as hereinbefore mentioned or not,`
  line `who sells goods belonging to any principal whether disclosed or not; and`
  line
  line `(iv) an auctioneer who sells or auctions goods belonging to any principal, whether disclosed`
  line `or not and whether the offer of the intending purchaser is accepted by him or by the principal or a`
  line `nominee of the principal;`
  line
  line `(f) "Delhi" means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(g) "goods" includes all materials, articles, commodities and all other kinds of moveable property,`
  line `but does not include newspapers, actionable claims, stocks, shares, securities or money;`
  line
  line `(h) "manufacture", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means producing,`
  line `making, extracting, altering, ornamenting, finishing or otherwise processing, treating or adapting any`
  line `goods, but does not include any such process or mode of manufacture as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(i) "Official Gazette" means the Delhi Gazette;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "registered" means registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "sale", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means any transfer of`
  line `property in goods by one person to another for cash or for deferred payment or for other valuable`
  line `consideration, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a transfer of goods on hire-purchase or other system of payment by instalments, but does`
  line `not include a mortgage or hypothecation of, or a charge or pledge on, goods;`
  line
  line `(ii) supply of goods by a society (including a co-operative society), club, firm or any`
  line `association to its members for cash or for deferred payment, or for commission, remuneration`
  line `or other valuable consideration, whether or not in the course of business; and`
  line
  line `(iii) transfer of goods by an auctioneer referred to in sub-clause (iv) of clause (e);`
  line
  line `(m) "sale price" means the amount payable to a dealer as consideration for the sale of any goods,`
  line `less any sum allowed as cash discount according to the practice normally prevailing in trade, but`
  line `inclusive of any sum charged for anything done by the dealer in respect of goods at the time of or`
  line `before the delivery thereof other than the cost of freight or delivery or the cost of installation in cases`
  line `where such cost is separately charged;`
  line
  line `(n) "tax" means sales tax payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "turnover" means the aggregate of the amounts of sale price receivable, or, if a dealer so`
  line `elects, actually received by the dealer, in respect of any sale of goods made during any prescribed`
  line `period in any year after deducting the amount of sale price, if any, refunded by the dealer to a`
  line `purchaser in respect of any goods purchased and returned by the purchaser within the prescribed`
  line `period:`
  line
  line `Provided that an election as aforesaid once made shall not be altered except with the permission`
  line `of the Commissioner and on such terms and conditions as he may think fit to impose;`
  line
  line `(p) "year" means the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (33113)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Incidence of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33113&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every dealer whose turnover during the year immediately preceding the`
  line `commencement of this Act exceeds the taxable quantum and every denier who at the commencement of`
  line `this Act, is registered or is liable to pay tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956), shall be`
  line `liable to pay tax under this Act on all sales effected by him on or after such commencement.`
  line
  line `(2) Every dealer to whom sub-section (1) does not apply, shall--`
  line
  line `(i) with effect from the date immediately following the day on which his turnover calculated from`
  line `the commencement of any year first exceeds within such year the taxable quantum, be liable to pay`
  line `tax under this Act on all sales effected by him after that day;`
  line
  line `(ii) if he becomes liable to pay tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956) or is`
  line `registered as a dealer under the said Act at any time after the commencement of this Act, be liable to`
  line `pay tax on all sales effected by him or on his behalf within Delhi on or after the date he becomes so`
  line `liable or is registered under the said Act, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) Every dealer who has become liable to pay tax under this Act shall continue to be so liable until`
  line `the expiry of three consecutive years during each of which his turnover has failed to exceed the taxable`
  line `quantum and such further period after the date of such expiry as may be prescribed and on the expiry of`
  line `such further period his liability to pay tax shall cease:`
  line
  line `Provided that any dealer may, after the expiry of one year following the year in which his turnover`
  line `has failed to exceed the taxable quantum, apply for the cancellation of his certificate of registration, and`
  line `on such cancellation, his liability to pay tax shall cease:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in respect of any goods purchased by any dealer before the date of such`
  line `cancellation and remaining unsold or unutilised for the purpose for which they were purchased, he shall`
  line `be liable to pay so much of tax as would have been payable had he not been registered as a dealer on the`
  line `date of purchase of such goods.`
  line
  line `(4) Every dealer whose liability to pay tax under this Act has ceased under sub-section (3), shall, if`
  line `his turnover calculated from the commencement of any year again exceeds the taxable quantum on any`
  line `day within such year, be liable to pay such tax with effect from the date immediately following the day on`
  line `which his turnover first exceeds the taxable quantum, on all sales effected by him after that day.`
  line
  line `(5) Any dealer whose certificate of registration has been cancelled under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 20, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) if his turnover calculated from the date of cancellation of such certificate exceeds the taxable`
  line `quantum on any day within the year; or`
  line
  line `(b) if his turnover calculated from the commencement of any subsequent year, exceeds the`
  line `taxable quantum on any day within the year,`
  line
  line `be liable to pay tax under this Act with effect from the date immediately following the day on which such`
  line `turnover again first exceeds the taxable quantum on all sales effected by him after that day of goods`
  line `imported by him from outside Delhi or manufactured by him in Delhi or purchased by him without`
  line `payment of tax leviable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) No dealer who deals exclusively in one or more classes of goods specified in the Third`
  line `Schedule shall be liable to pay any tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) For the purposes of this Act, "taxable quantum" means, --`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to any dealer who imports for sale any goods into Delhi. . . . . Nil,`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to any dealer who manufactures goods for sale regardless of the value of goods`
  line `manufactured . . . . . . . . . Rs. 30,000.00,`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to any other dealer . . . . . . Rs. 1,00,000.00:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Administrator is of opinion that having regard to the difficulty in maintaining`
  line `accounts or for any other sufficient cause the taxable quantum in respect of any class of dealers falling`
  line `under clause (b) should be increased, the Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix in`
  line `respect of such class of dealers such taxable quantum, not exceeding rupees one lakh, as may be specified`
  line `in the notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of computation of taxable quantum under sub-section (7), the`
  line `turnover of all sales effected by a dealer shall be taken into account irrespective of whether such sales are`
  line `taxable under this Act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (33114)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Rate of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33114&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tax payable by a dealer under this Act shall be levied--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of taxable turnover in respect of the goods specified in the First Schedule, at the`
  line `rate of twelve paise in the rupee;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of taxable turnover in respect of the goods specified in the Second Schedule, at`
  line `such rate not exceeding four paise in rupee as the Central Government may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, determine;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of taxable turnover in respect of any food or drink served for consumption in a`
  line `hotel or restaurant or part thereof, with which a cabaret, floor show or similar entertainment is`
  line `provided therein, at the rate of forty paise in the rupee;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of taxable turnover in respect of any other goods, at the rate of seven paise in the`
  line `rupee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrator may with the previous approval of the Central Government and by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, add to, or omit from, or otherwise amend, the First Schedule or the`
  line `Second Schedule, either retrospectively or prospectively, and thereupon the First Schedule or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Second Schedule, shall be deemed to be amended accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such amendment shall be made retrospectively if it would have the effect of`
  line `prejudicially affecting the interests of any dealer:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in respect of any goods or class of goods the Administrator is of the opinion that it`
  line `is expedient in the interest of the general public so to do, he may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the tax in respect of taxable`
  line `turnover of such goods or class of goods shall, subject to such conditions as may be specified, be levied at`
  line `such modified rate not exceeding the rate applicable under this section, as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, "taxable turnover" means that part of a dealer's turnover during the`
  line `prescribed period in any year which remains after deducting therefrom,--`
  line
  line `(a) his turnover during that period on--`
  line
  line `(i) sale of goods, the point of sale at which such goods shall be taxable is specified by`
  line `the Administrator under section 5 and in respect of which due tax is shown to the satisfaction of`
  line `the Commissioner to have been paid;`
  line
  line `(ii) sale of goods declared tax-free under section 7;`
  line
  line `(iii) sale of goods not liable to tax under section 8;`
  line
  line `(iv) sale of goods which are proved to the satisfaction of the Commissioner to have been`
  line `purchased within a period of twelve months prior to the date of registration of the dealer`
  line `and subjected to tax under the Bengal Finance (Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as`
  line `it was then in force, or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) sale to a registered dealer--`
  line
  line `(A) of goods of the class or classes specified in the certificate of registration of such`
  line `dealer, as being intended for use by him as raw materials in the manufacture in Delhi of any`
  line `goods, other than goods specified in the Third Schedule, or newspapers,--`
  line
  line `(1) for sale by him inside Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(2) for sale by him in the course of inter-State trade or commerce, being a sale`
  line `occasioning, or effected by transfer of documents of title to such goods during the`
  line `movement of such goods from Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(3) for sale by him in the course of export outside India being a sale occasioning the`
  line `movement of such goods from Delhi, or a sale effected by transfer of documents of title`
  line `to such goods effected during the movement of such goods from Delhi, to a place outside`
  line `India and after the goods have crossed the customs frontiers of India; or`
  line
  line `(B) of goods of the class or classes specified in the certificate of registration of such`
  line `dealer as being intended for resale by him in Delhi, or for sale by him in the course of`
  line `inter-State trade or commerce or in the course of export outside India in the manner specified`
  line `in sub-item (2) or sub-item (3) of item (A), as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(C) of containers or other materials, used for the packing of goods, of the class or classes`
  line `specified in the certificate of registration of such dealer, other than goods specified in the`
  line `Third Schedule, intended for sale or resale;`
  line
  line `(vi) such other sales as are exempt from payment of tax under section 66 or as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no deduction in respect of any sale referred to in sub-clause (iv) shall be allowed`
  line `unless the goods, in respect of which deduction is claimed, are proved to have been sold by the dealer`
  line `within a period of twelve months from the date of his registration and the claim for such deduction is`
  line `included in the return required to be furnished by the dealer in respect of the said sale:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no deduction in respect of any sale referred to in sub-clause (v) shall be`
  line `allowed unless a true declaration duly filled and signed by the registered dealer to whom the goods`
  line `are sold and containing the prescribed particulars in the prescribed form obtainable from the`
  line `prescribed authority is furnished in the prescribed manner and within the prescribed time, by the`
  line `dealer who sells the goods:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where any goods are purchased by a registered dealer for any of the`
  line `purposes mentioned in sub-clause (v), but are not so utilised by him, the price of the goods so`
  line `purchased shall be allowed to be deducted from the turnover of the selling dealer but shall be included`
  line `in the taxable turnover of the purchasing dealer; and`
  line
  line `(b) the tax collected by the dealer under this Act as such and shown separately in`
  line `cash memoranda or bills, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (33115)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Administrator to prescribe points at which goods may be taxed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33115&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in this Act, the Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette and subject`
  line `to such conditions, if any, as may be specified therein, specify the point of sale at which any goods or`
  line `class of goods may be taxed, and on the issue of such notification, the points of sale in relation to any`
  line `such goods or class of goods other than the point of sale so notified, shall be exempt from payment of tax`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exemption shall be allowed unless a true declaration duly filled and signed by`
  line `the registered dealer by whom the goods are sold and containing the prescribed particulars in the`
  line `prescribed form obtainable from the prescribed authority is furnished in the prescribed manner and within`
  line `the prescribed time, by the dealer who purchases the goods:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Administrator may, if he is of opinion that it is necessary in the public`
  line `interest so to do, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt, subject to such restrictions and`
  line `conditions as may be specified therein, any dealer or class of dealers from furnishing a declaration under`
  line `the first proviso.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (33116)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33116&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The burden of proving that in respect of any sale effected by a dealer he is not`
  line `liable to pay tax under this Act, shall lie on him.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (33117)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Tax-free goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33117&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No tax shall be payable under this Act on the sale of goods specified in the`
  line `Third Schedule subject to the conditions and exceptions, if any, set out therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, add to, or omit from, or otherwise amend, the Third Schedule either`
  line `retrospectively or prospectively, and thereupon the Third Schedule shall be deemed to be amended`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such amendment shall be made retrospectively if it would have the effect of`
  line `prejudicially affecting the interests of any dealer.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (33118)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Certain sales and purchases not liable to tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33118&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder shall be deemed to impose, or authorise the imposition of a tax on any sale or purchase of any`
  line `goods when such sale or purchase takes place--`
  line
  line `(i) in the course of inter-State trade or commerce; or`
  line
  line `(ii) outside Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the course of the import of the goods into, or export of the goods out of, the territory of`
  line India.
  line
  line `Explanation.--Sections 3, 4, and 5 of the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956) shall apply for`
  line `determining whether or not a particular sale or purchase takes place in the manner indicated in clause (i),`
  line `clause (ii) or clause (iii) of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (33119)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Sales tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33119&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For carrying out the purposes of this Act, the Administrator shall`
  line `appoint a person to be the Commissioner of Sales Tax.`
  line
  line `(2) To assist the Commissioner in the execution of his functions under this Act, the Administrator`
  line `may appoint as many Additional Commissioners of Sales Tax, Sales Tax Officers and such other persons`
  line `with such designations as the Administrator thinks necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall have jurisdiction over the whole of Delhi and the other persons appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) shall have jurisdiction over such areas as the Commissioner may specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner and other persons appointed under sub-section (2) shall exercise such powers`
  line `as may be conferred, and perform such duties as may be required, by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (33120)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Delegation of Commissioner’s powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33120&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such restrictions and conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed, the Commissioner may, by order in writing, delegate any of his powers under this Act except`
  line `those under sub-section (3) of section 9 and sub-section (1) of section 52 to any person appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9:`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers of the Commissioner under clauses (i) to (vi) (both inclusive)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 41 shall not be delegated to any person lower in rank than that of a Sales Tax`
  line `Officer, and those under sub-section (1) of section 49 shall not be delegated to any person other than an`
  line `Additional Commissioner of Sales Tax appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (33121)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to transfer proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33121&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, by order in writing, transfer any`
  line `proceedings or class of proceedings under any provision of this Act from any person appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9 to any other person so appointed whether or not such other person has`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of the area to which such proceedings or class of proceedings relate, and the`
  line `Commissioner may likewise transfer any such proceedings (including a proceeding already transferred`
  line `under this section) from any such person to himself.`
  line
  line `(2) The person to whom any proceeding is transferred under sub-section (1) shall proceed to dispose`
  line `it of as if it had been initiated by himself.`
  line
  line `(3) The transfer of a proceeding shall not render necessary the reissue of any notice already issued`
  line `before such transfer and the person to whom the proceeding is transferred may, in his discretion, continue`
  line `it from the stage at which it was left by the person from whom it was transferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "proceedings" in relation to any person whose name`
  line `is specified in any order issued thereunder, means all proceedings under this Act in respect of any year`
  line `which may be pending on the date of such order or which may have been completed on or before such`
  line `date, and includes also such proceedings which may be commenced after the date of such order in respect`
  line `of any year.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (33122)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Disputes regarding territorial jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33122&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be entitled to call in question`
  line `the jurisdiction of any sales tax authority appointed under section 9, not being an appellate authority, after`
  line `the expiry of ninety days from the date of receipt by that person of any notice under this Act issued by`
  line `such sales tax authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any objection as to the jurisdiction of any such sales tax authority may be raised within the period`
  line `aforesaid by submitting a memorandum to the authority concerned who shall refer the question to the`
  line `Commissioner and the Commissioner shall after giving the person raising the objection a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, make an order determining the question and his decision in this behalf shall`
  line `be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (33123)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33123&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, constitute an Appellate Tribunal consisting of one or more members, as it`
  line `thinks fit, to exercise the powers and discharge the functions conferred on the Appellate Tribunal by or`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Appellate Tribunal consists of one member, that member shall be a person`
  line `who has held a civil judicial post for at least ten years or who has been a member of the Central Legal`
  line `Service (not below Grade III) for at least three years or who has been in practice as an advocate for at`
  line `least ten years, and where the Appellate Tribunal consists of more than one member, one`
  line `such member shall be a person qualified as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the number of members of the Appellate Tribunal is more than one, the Central`
  line `Government shall appoint one of those members to be the Chairman of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the qualifications and other conditions of service of`
  line `the member or members constituting the Appellate Tribunal and the period for which such member`
  line `or members shall hold office, shall be such as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Any vacancy in the membership of the Appellate Tribunal shall be filled up by the Central`
  line `Government as soon as practicable.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the number of members of the Appellate Tribunal is more than one and if the members`
  line `differ in opinion on any point, the point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority, if there`
  line `is a majority, but if the members are equally divided, the decision of the Chairman of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the previous sanction of the Central Government, the Appellate Tribunal shall, for the`
  line `purpose of regulating its procedure and disposal of its business, make regulations consistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(7) The regulations made under sub-section (6) shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(8) The Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purpose of discharging its functions, have all the powers`
  line `which are vested in the Commissioner under section 42 and any proceeding before the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for`
  line `the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (33124)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1978, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "points of sale" (w.e.f. 26-11-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33124&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) No dealer shall, while being liable to pay tax under section 3, carry on`
  line `business as a dealer unless he has been registered and possesses a certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Every dealer required by sub-section (1) to be registered shall make an application for registration`
  line `within such time, in such manner and to such authority, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the said authority is satisfied that the application is in order, it shall, in accordance with such`
  line `rules as may be prescribed, register the applicant within the prescribed period and grant him a certificate`
  line `of registration in the prescribed form which shall specify the goods or class of goods for the purposes of`
  line `sub-clause (v) of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the said authority is of opinion that the application is not in order, it shall, by an order`
  line `passed within the said period and for reasons to be recorded in writing, reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no goods or class of goods in respect of which the ^1[point of sale] has been`
  line `specified by the Administrator under section 5 shall be specified in a certificate of registration, and where`
  line `a notification is issued under that section subsequent to the grant of any certificate of registration in`
  line `respect of any goods or class of goods specified in a certificate, if the said certificate shall be deemed to`
  line `have been amended to omit the references to such goods or class of goods.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the goods or class of goods to be specified in`
  line `a certificate of registration granted under sub-section (3) of this section or sub-section (2) of section 16`
  line `shall not include goods referred to in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (33125)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Voluntary registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33125&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dealer, other than a dealer who deals exclusively in one or`
  line `more classes of goods specified in the Third Schedule, whose turnover during a year exceeds twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees may, notwithstanding that he may not be liable to pay tax under section 3, apply for`
  line `registration under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 14 shall, as far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to registration of dealers under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every dealer who has been registered under this section shall, for so long as his registration`
  line `remains in force, be liable to pay tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The registration of a dealer under this section shall be in force for a period of not less than three`
  line `complete years and shall remain in force thereafter unless cancelled under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (33126)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Provisional registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33126&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who intends to establish a business in Delhi for the`
  line `purpose of manufacturing goods of a value exceeding thirty thousand rupees per year, may,`
  line `notwithstanding that he is not required to be registered under section 14, apply for provisional registration`
  line `in such manner and to such authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If the said authority, after making such inquiry as it may consider necessary, is satisfied as to the`
  line `bona fide intention of the person making the application, it may, subject to such restrictions and`
  line `conditions as it may impose, grant a provisional certificate of registration on such person furnishing such`
  line `security as it may consider necessary and shall specify in such certificate the goods or class of goods for`
  line `the purposes of sub-clause (v) of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who has been granted a provisional certificate of registration under this section`
  line `shall, for so long as such certificate is in force, be liable to pay tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) A provisional certificate of registration granted under this section shall be in force for such period`
  line `as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(5) The authority prescribed under sub-section (1) may, on application made in this behalf in the`
  line `prescribed manner and subject to such restrictions and conditions as it may impose, extend, from time to`
  line `time, the period specified in the provisional certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of section 18 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to security required to be`
  line `furnished under sub-section (2) of this section.`
  line
  line `(7) If a person, who has been granted a provisional certificate of registration under this section, fails`
  line `without sufficient cause to establish a business within the period specified in such certificate or fails to`
  line `comply with any of the restrictions or conditions subject to which such certificate was granted, he shall be`
  line `liable to pay a penalty equal to one and a half times the amount of tax which would have been payable`
  line `had he not been so registered under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (33127)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Special registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33127&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No dealer shall, while being liable to pay tax under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 3, carry on business as a dealer unless he has obtained a special certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Every dealer required to be registered under sub-section (1) shall make an application for`
  line `registration within such time, in such manner and to such authority, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the said authority is satisfied that the application is in order, it shall, in accordance with such`
  line `rules as may be prescribed, grant a special certificate of registration to the applicant in the prescribed`
  line `form:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said authority shall not specify in any such certificate the goods or class of goods`
  line `for the purposes of sub-clause (v) of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (33128)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Security from certain class of dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33128&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, if it appears to him to be`
  line `necessary so to do for the proper realisation of the tax, composition money or other dues payable under`
  line `this Act or for the proper custody and use of the forms referred to in the second proviso to clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 4, or the first proviso to section 5, as the case may be, impose, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing as a condition of the grant of the certificate of registration under section 14, section 15`
  line `or section 17 to a dealer or of the continuance in effect of such certificate granted to any dealer, a`
  line `requirement that the dealer shall furnish in the prescribed manner and within such time as may be`
  line `specified in the order such security or, as the case may be, such additional security as may be so specified,`
  line `for all or any of the aforesaid purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) No dealer shall be required to furnish any security or additional security under sub-section (1)`
  line `unless he has been given an opportunity of being heard and the amount of security or additional security`
  line `that may be required to be furnished, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a dealer liable to pay tax under sub-section (2) of section 3 who has applied for`
  line `the grant of a certificate of registration under section 14, be such amount as the Commissioner may,`
  line `having regard to the nature and size of the business of such dealer, determine for the payment of the`
  line `tax for which the dealer may be or become liable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where security is to be given for the proper custody and use of the forms referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1), be the amount of tax determined by the Commissioner which is likely to be saved`
  line `by a dealer by the issue of such forms;`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, not exceed the tax payable, in accordance with the estimate of the`
  line `Commissioner on the taxable turnover of the dealer,`
  line
  line `for the year in which such security or additional security is required to be furnished.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the security or additional security furnished by a dealer is in the form of a security bond`
  line `and the surety dies or becomes insolvent, the dealer shall, within thirty days of the occurrence of such`
  line `event, inform the authority granting the certificate of registration and shall, within ninety days of such`
  line `occurrence, execute a fresh surety bond.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner may by order, for good and sufficient cause, and after giving the dealer an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, forfeit the whole or any part of the security furnished by a dealer.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, by reason of an order under sub-section (4), the security furnished by any dealer is`
  line `forfeited in whole or is rendered insufficient, he shall furnish a fresh security of the requisite amount or,`
  line `as the case may be, shall make up the deficiency in such manner and within such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (33129)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Amendment of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1978, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "the firm who changed constitution" (w.e.f. 26-11-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33129&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, after considering any`
  line `information furnished under this Act or otherwise received and after making such inquiry as he may deem`
  line `fit, amend from time to time any certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) An amendment of the certificate of registration made under sub-section (1) shall take effect:--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a change in the name, ownership or place of business, or opening of a new place`
  line `of business, from the date of contingency which necessitates the amendment whether or not`
  line `information in that behalf is furnished within the time prescribed under section 40;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any addition or modification in the description of any goods or class of goods in`
  line `the certificate of registration, from the date of the contingency if information in that behalf is`
  line `furnished within the time prescribed under section 40 and from the date of receipt of request for such`
  line `addition or modification by the Commissioner, in any other case;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of deletion of any goods or class of goods, from the date of order of deletion:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall, before amending on his own motion a certificate of`
  line `registration, give the dealer affected by such amendment a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where in consequence of a change in the ownership of a business the liability to`
  line `pay tax of a dealer ceases, the amendment of the certificate of registration shall take effect from the date`
  line `on which information in respect of such change is furnished under section 40.`
  line
  line `(3) Any amendment of a certificate of registration under this section shall be without prejudice to any`
  line `liability for tax or penalty imposable, or for any prosecution for an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where a registered dealer--`
  line
  line `(a) effects a change in the name of his business; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a firm and there is a change in the constitution of the firm without dissolution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) is a trustee of a trust and there is a change in the trustees thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) is a guardian of a ward and there is a change in the guardian; or`
  line
  line `(e) is a Hindu undivided family and the business of such family is converted into a partnership`
  line `business with all or any of the co-parceners as partners thereof,`
  line
  line `then, merely by reason of any of the circumstances aforesaid, it shall not be necessary for the dealer, or`
  line `^1[the firm which changed the constitution] or the new trustees, or the new guardian, or as the case may be,`
  line `the partners of such partnership business, to apply for a fresh certificate of registration and on information`
  line `being furnished in the manner required by section 40 the certificate of registration shall be amended.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (33130)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Cancellation of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33130&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) any business in respect of which a certificate of registration has been granted to a dealer under`
  line `this Act, is discontinued; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of transfer of business by a dealer, the transferee already holds a certificate of`
  line `registration under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) a dealer has ceased to be liable to pay tax under this Act,`
  line
  line `the Commissioner may cancel the certificate of registration of such dealer or the transferor, as the case`
  line `may be, from such date as may be specified by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case referred to in clause (a) or clause (b), the certificate of registration shall be`
  line `deemed to be inoperative with effect from the date of discontinuance or transfer of the business, as the`
  line `case may be, and in a case referred to in clause (c), from the date on which the dealer's liability to pay tax`
  line `has ceased, notwithstanding the fact that the order of cancellation is passed or that the particulars of the`
  line `dealer regarding cancellation are published, as required by section 65, in the Official Gazette, after the`
  line `aforesaid date:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a dealer has failed to furnish information regarding discontinuance of his`
  line `business as required by section 40, the Commissioner shall before cancelling the certificate from any`
  line `specified date, publish in the Official Gazette, a notice of his intention so to do for the information of the`
  line `dealer and shall hear objections, if any, of the dealer before passing the order.`
  line
  line `(2) A dealer registered under section 15 may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (4) of that`
  line `section, apply in the prescribed manner not later than six months before the end of a year to the`
  line `Commissioner for cancellation of his certificate of registration and the Commissioner shall, unless the`
  line `dealer is liable to pay tax under section 3, cancel the certificate of registration accordingly, and such`
  line `cancellation shall take effect from the end of the year.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Commissioner may at any`
  line `time for reasons to be recorded in writing and after giving the dealer an opportunity of being heard, cancel`
  line `the certificate of registration held by such dealer from such date as the Commissioner may specify in this`
  line behalf--
  line
  line `(a) if the dealer has failed to pay any tax (including any penalty) due from him under any`
  line `provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the dealer holds or accepts or furnishes or causes to be furnished a declaration for the`
  line `purposes of sub-clause (v) of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4 or section 5 which he knows or`
  line `has reason to believe to be false; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the dealer who has been required to furnish the security under the provisions of section 18`
  line `has failed to furnish such security; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the dealer contravenes or has contravened any of the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(e) if the dealer has been convicted of an offence under this Act or under the Bengal Finance`
  line `(Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as then in force in Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(f) if there is any other reason which in the opinion of the Commissioner warrants such`
  line cancellation.
  line
  line `(4) (a) If an order of cancellation passed under sub-section (3) is set aside as a result of an appeal or`
  line `other proceeding under this Act, the certificate of registration of the dealer shall be restored and he shall`
  line `be liable to pay tax as if his certificate had not been cancelled.`
  line
  line `(b) If any dealer whose certificate of registration has been restored under clause (a) satisfies the`
  line `Commissioner that tax has been paid by such dealer on sale of goods made to him during the period his`
  line `certificate of registration was inoperative which, but for the cancellation of such certificate he would not`
  line `have paid, then the amount of such tax shall be adjusted or refunded in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Every dealer who applies for cancellation of his registration shall surrender with his application`
  line `the certificate of registration granted to him and every dealer whose registration is cancelled otherwise`
  line `than on the basis of his application shall surrender the certificate of registration within seven days of the`
  line `date of communication to him of the order of cancellation.`
  line
  line `(6) If a dealer fails to surrender his certificate of registration as provided in sub-section (5), the`
  line `Commissioner may, by an order in writing and after giving the dealer an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `direct that the dealer shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum not exceeding twenty-five rupees for every day`
  line `of default.`
  line
  line `(7) The cancellation of a certificate of registration shall not affect the liability of any person to pay tax`
  line `due for any period prior to the date of such cancellation, whether such tax is assessed before the date of`
  line `cancellation but remains unpaid or is assessed thereafter notwithstanding that he is not liable to pay tax`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) Where by any order passed under this Act it is found that any person registered as a dealer ought`
  line `not to have been so registered, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, such person shall be`
  line `liable to pay tax for the period commencing with the date of his registration and ending with the date of`
  line `such order, as if he were a dealer.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (33131)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Periodical payment of tax and filing of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33131&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Tax payable under this Act shall be paid`
  line `in the manner hereinafter provided at such intervals as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every registered dealer and every other dealer who may be required so to do by the Commissioner`
  line `by notice served in the prescribed manner shall furnish such returns of turnover by such dates and to such`
  line `authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every registered dealer required to furnish returns under sub-section (2) shall pay into a`
  line `Government Treasury or the Reserve Bank of India or in such other manner as may be prescribed, the full`
  line `amount of tax due from him under this Act according to such return, and shall where such payment is`
  line `made into a Government Treasury or the Reserve Bank of India furnish along with the return a receipt`
  line `from such Treasury or Bank showing the payment of such amount.`
  line
  line `(4) If any registered dealer discovers any mistake or error in any return furnished by him, he may at`
  line `any time, before the expiry of three months next following the last date prescribed for furnishing of the`
  line `return, furnish a revised return, and if the revised return shows a higher amount of tax to be due than`
  line `was shown in the original return, it shall be accompanied by a receipt showing payment in the manner`
  line `provided in sub-section (3) of the excess amount.`
  line
  line `(5) Every return under this section shall be signed and verified--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an individual, by the individual himself, and where the individual is absent from`
  line `India by the individual concerned or by some person duly authorised by him in this behalf and where`
  line `the individual is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by his guardian or by`
  line `any other person competent to act on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, by a Karta, and where the Karta is absent from India`
  line `or is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by any other adult member of such family;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a company or local authority, by the principal officer thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a firm, by any partner thereof, not being a minor;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of any other association, by any member of the association or the principal officer`
  line `thereof; and`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of any other person, by that person or by some person competent to act on his`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of sub-section (5) of this section and section 59 the expression "principal`
  line `officer" shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause (35) of section 2 of the Income-Tax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (33132)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Collection of tax only by registered dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33132&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who is not a registered dealer shall`
  line `collect in respect of any sale of goods by him in Delhi any amount by way of tax under this Act, and no`
  line `registered dealer shall make any such collection except in accordance with this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a dealer who has been permitted by the`
  line `Commissioner to make a lump sum payment under section 29 shall not collect any sum by way of tax on`
  line `the sale of goods if made during the period of which such lump sum payment relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (33133)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33133&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of tax due from a registered dealer shall be assessed separately for`
  line `each year during which he is liable to pay the tax:`
  line
  line `Provided that when such dealer fails to furnish a return relating to any period of a year by the`
  line `prescribed date, the Commissioner may, if he thinks fit, assess the tax due from such dealer separately for`
  line `that period or any other period of such year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Commissioner may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, assess the tax due from any dealer for a part of a year.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner is satisfied that the returns furnished in respect of any period are correct and`
  line `complete, he shall assess the amount of tax due from the dealer on the basis of such returns.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) If the Commissioner is not satisfied that the returns furnished in respect of any period are`
  line `correct and complete and he thinks it necessary to require the presence of the dealer or the production of`
  line `further evidence, he shall serve on such dealer in the prescribed manner a notice requiring him on a date`
  line `and at a place specified therein either to attend and produce or cause to be produced all evidence on which`
  line `such dealer relies in support of his returns, or to produce such evidence as is specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(b) On the date specified in the notice, or as soon as may be thereafter, the Commissioner shall, after`
  line `considering all the evidence which may be produced, assess the amount of tax due from the dealer.`
  line
  line `(4) If a dealer fails to comply with the terms of any notice issued under sub-section (3), the`
  line `Commissioner shall assess to the best of his judgment the amount of tax, if any, due from him.`
  line
  line `(5) If a dealer fails to furnish returns in respect of any period by the prescribed date, the`
  line `Commissioner shall, after giving the dealer a reasonable opportunity of being heard, assess to the best`
  line `of his judgment the amount of tax, if any, due from him.`
  line
  line `(6) If, upon information which has come into his possession, the Commissioner is satisfied that any`
  line `dealer who has been liable to pay tax under this Act in respect of any period, has failed to get himself`
  line `registered under section 14 or section 17, as the case may be, the Commissioner shall proceed in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed to assess to the best of his judgment the amount of tax due from the dealer`
  line `in respect of such period and all subsequent periods and in making such assessment shall give the dealer a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, and the Commissioner may, if he is satisfied that the default was`
  line `made without reasonable cause, direct that the dealer shall pay, by way of penalty, in addition to the`
  line `amount of the tax so assessed, a sum not exceeding twice that amount.`
  line
  line `(7) No assessment under the provisions of sub-sections (1) to (5) shall be made after the expiry of`
  line `four years, and no assessment under the provisions of sub-section (6) shall be made after the expiry of six`
  line `years from the end of the year in respect of which or part of which the tax is assessable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such assessment is made in consequence of or to give effect to, any order of an`
  line `appellate or revisional authority or of a court, the period of four years or six years, as the case may`
  line `be, shall be reckoned from the date of such order and further that the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 24 regarding time limit for service of notice shall not apply for assessment made under this`
  line proviso.
  line
  line `(8) Any assessment made under this section shall be without prejudice to any prosecution for an`
  line `offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (33134)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Turnover escaping assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33134&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where after a dealer has been assessed under section 23 for`
  line `any year or part thereof, the Commissioner has reason to believe that the whole or any part of the turnover`
  line `of a dealer in respect of any period has escaped assessment to tax or has been under-assessed or has been`
  line `assessed at a rate lower than the rate at which it is assessable, or any deduction has been wrongly made`
  line `therefrom, the Commissioner may--`
  line
  line `(a) within six years from the date of final order of assessment, in a case where the dealer has`
  line `concealed, omitted or failed to disclose fully the particulars of such turnover; and`
  line
  line `(b) within four years from the date of final order of assessment, in any other case,`
  line
  line `serve a notice on the dealer and after giving the dealer an opportunity of being heard and making such`
  line `inquiry as he considers necessary, proceed to determine to the best of his judgment, the amount of tax due`
  line `from the dealer in respect of such turnover, and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, production before the Commissioner of account books`
  line `or other evidence from which material evidence could with due diligence have been discovered by the`
  line `Commissioner will not necessarily amount to disclosure within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of assessment, reassessment or re-computation shall be made under sub-section (1),`
  line after--
  line
  line `(a) the expiry of four years or, as the case may be, six years as specified in sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 23; or`
  line
  line `(b) the expiry of one year from the date of service of notice under sub-section (1),`
  line
  line `whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (33135)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Payment and recovery of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33135&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of tax--`
  line
  line `(a) due where returns have been furnished without the receipt showing full payment thereof; and`
  line
  line `(b) assessed, reassessed or re-computed for any period under section 23 or section 24, less the`
  line `amount if any, already paid by the dealer in respect of the said period,`
  line
  line `shall together with any penalty that may be directed to be paid under any of the provisions of this`
  line `section, sub-section (6) of section 23, section 55, section 56 or section 57 be paid by the dealer or the`
  line `person liable therefor into a Government Treasury or the Reserve Bank of India or in such other manner`
  line `as may be prescribed within thirty days from the date of service of notice of demand issued by the`
  line `Commissioner for this purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner has reason to believe that it will be detrimental to revenue if`
  line `the full period of thirty days aforesaid is allowed, he may direct that the sum specified in the notice of`
  line `demand shall be paid within such period being a period less than the period of thirty days aforesaid, as`
  line `may be specified by him in that notice.`
  line
  line `(2) On an application made before the expiry of the due date under sub-section (1), the Commissioner`
  line `may, in respect of any particular dealer or person and for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the`
  line `time for payment or allow payment by instalments or grant stay, subject to such conditions as he may`
  line `think fit to impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) If the amount of tax and penalty, if any, is not paid within the time specified in sub-section (1) or`
  line `extended under sub-section (2), as the case may be, the dealer or the person liable therefor shall be`
  line `deemed to be in default in respect of that amount.`
  line
  line `(4) In a case where payment by instalments is allowed under sub-section (2) and the dealer or the`
  line `person liable for such payment commits default in paying any one of the instalments within the time fixed`
  line `under that sub-section, the dealer or the person aforesaid shall be deemed to be in default in respect of the`
  line `whole of the amount then outstanding and the other instalment or instalments shall be deemed to have`
  line `been due on the same date as the instalment actually in default.`
  line
  line `(5) When a dealer or a person is in default or is deemed to be in default in making payment of tax and`
  line `penalty, if any, he shall, in addition to the amount of arrears payable under the foregoing sub-sections, be`
  line `liable to pay, by way of penalty, an amount which in the case of a continuing default may be increased,`
  line `from time to time, so however, that total amount of penalty does not exceed the amount in arrears:`
  line
  line `Provided that before levying any such penalty, the dealer or the person aforesaid shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(6) Where as a result of any final order the amount of tax and penalty, if any, with respect to the`
  line `default, in the payment of which the penalty was levied, has been wholly reduced, the penalty levied shall`
  line `be cancelled and the amount of penalty paid shall be refunded.`
  line
  line `(7) Any amount of tax or penalty in respect of which a dealer or person is in default, or any`
  line `composition money due under section 29 or section 54 which remains unpaid, shall be recoverable as an`
  line `arrear of land revenue:`
  line
  line `Provided that where security, other than in the form of surety bond, has been furnished by a dealer`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 16 or section 18, the Commissioner may, for good and sufficient reasons`
  line `in writing, realise any amount of tax or penalty or composition money remaining unpaid as aforesaid or`
  line `part thereof by ordering forfeiture of the whole or any part of the security.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (33136)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Continuation of certain recovery proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33136&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice of demand in respect of any`
  line `tax or penalty or any other amount payable under this Act (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `"government dues") is served upon any dealer, and any appeal, revision application or other proceeding is`
  line `filed or taken in respect of such government dues, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) where such government dues are enhanced in such appeal, revision or other proceeding, the`
  line `Commissioner shall serve upon the dealer another notice of demand only in respect of the amount by`
  line `which such government dues are enhanced and any recovery proceedings in relation to such`
  line `government dues as are covered by the notice of demand served upon him before the disposal of such`
  line `appeal, revision application or proceeding may, without the service of any fresh notice of demand, be`
  line `continued from the stage at which such proceedings stood immediately before such disposal;`
  line
  line `(b) where such government dues are reduced in such appeal, revision or proceeding,--`
  line
  line `(i) it shall not be necessary for the Commissioner to serve upon the dealer a fresh notice of`
  line demand;
  line
  line `(ii) the Commissioner shall give intimation of such reduction to him and to the appropriate`
  line `authority with whom recovery proceedings are pending;`
  line
  line `(iii) any recovery proceedings initiated on the basis of the notice of demand served upon him`
  line `before the disposal of such appeal, revision application or proceeding may be continued in`
  line `relation to the amount so reduced from the stage at which such proceedings stood immediately`
  line `before such disposal.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (33137)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Interest.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33137&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any dealer fails to pay the tax due as required by sub-section (3) of section 21,`
  line `he shall, in addition to the tax (including any penalty) due, be liable to pay simple interest on the amount`
  line `so due at one per cent. per month from the date immediately following the last date for submission of the`
  line `return under sub-section (2) of the said section for a period of one month, and at one and a half per cent.`
  line `per month thereafter for so long as he continues to make default in such payment or till the date of`
  line `completion of assessment under section 23, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) When a dealer or a person is in default or is deemed to be in default in making the payment of tax,`
  line `he shall, in addition to the amounts payable under section 23 or section 24, be liable to pay simple interest`
  line `on such amount at one per cent. per month from the date of such default for a period of one month, and at`
  line `one and a half per cent. per month thereafter for so long as he continues to make default in the payment of`
  line `the said amount.`
  line
  line `(3) Where as a result of any final order the amount of tax (including any penalty) due or in default is`
  line `wholly reduced, the amount of interest, if any, paid shall be refunded, or if such amount is varied, the`
  line `interest due shall be calculated accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any amount of tax payable is enhanced by any such order, interest shall be`
  line `payable on the amount by which the tax is enhanced after the expiry of a period of three months from the`
  line `date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the realisation of any amount remains stayed by the order of any court or`
  line `authority and such order is subsequently vacated, interest shall be payable also for any period during`
  line `which such order remained in operation.`
  line
  line `(4) The interest payable under this section shall be deemed to be tax due under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (33138)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Special model of recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33138&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law or contract to`
  line `the contrary, the Commissioner may, at any time or from time to time, by notice in writing, a copy of`
  line `which shall be forwarded to the dealer at his last known address, require--`
  line
  line `(a) any person from whom any amount of money is due, or may become due, to a dealer on`
  line `whom notice has been served under sub-section (1) of section 25, or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who holds or may, subsequently hold money for or on account of such dealer,`
  line
  line `to pay to the Commissioner, either forthwith upon the money becoming due or being held or within the`
  line `time specified in the first mentioned notice (but not before the money becomes due or is held as aforesaid)`
  line `so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the amount due by the dealer in respect of the arrears of tax`
  line `and penalty under this Act, or the whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the amount of money due to a dealer from, or`
  line `money held for or on account of a dealer by, any person, shall be calculated by the Commissioner after`
  line `deducting therefrom such claims (if any) lawfully subsisting, as may have fallen due for payment by such`
  line `dealer to such person.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may amend or revoke any such notice or extend the time for making any`
  line `payment on pursuance of the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person making any payment in compliance with a notice under this section shall be deemed`
  line `to have made the payment under the authority of the dealer, and the receipt thereof by the`
  line `Commissioner shall constitute a good and sufficient discharge of the liability of such person to the extent`
  line `of the amount specified in the receipt.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person discharging any liability to the dealer after receipt of the notice referred to in this`
  line `section, shall be personally liable to the Commissioner to the extent of the liability discharged or to the`
  line `extent of the liability of the dealer for tax and penalty, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person to whom a notice under this section is sent, proves to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Commissioner that the sum demanded or any part thereof is not due to the dealer or that he does not hold`
  line `any money for or on account of the dealer, then, nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to`
  line `require such person to pay any such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(6) Any amount of money which the aforesaid person is required to pay to the Commissioner, or for`
  line `which he is personally liable to the Commissioner under this section shall, if it remains unpaid, be`
  line `recoverable as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(7) The Commissioner may apply to the court in whose custody there is money belonging to the`
  line `dealer for payment to him of the entire amount of such money or if it is more than the tax and penalty, if`
  line `any, due, an amount sufficient to discharge such tax and the penalty.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (33139)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Lump sum payment of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33139&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, in such circumstances and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, permit any dealer to pay in lieu of the amount of tax payable by him`
  line `under the provision of this Act, a lump sum determined in the prescribed manner, by way of composition.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (33140)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Refund.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33140&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person satisfies the Commissioner that the amount of tax paid by him or`
  line `on his behalf for any year exceeds the amount payable by him under this Act for that year, he shall, on`
  line `making a claim in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner, be entitled to refund of the`
  line `excess either by cash payment or at his option by deduction of such excess from the amount of tax and`
  line `penalty (if any) due in respect of any other period:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall first apply such excess towards the recovery of any amount in`
  line `respect of which a notice under section 25 has been issued and shall then refund the balance, if any.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- When no assessment is made, the due tax paid under section 21 by the dealer shall be`
  line `deemed to be the tax payable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where on account of death, incapacity, insolvency, liquidation or other cause a person is unable to`
  line `claim or receive any refund due to him, his legal representative or the trustee or guardian or receiver, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be entitled to claim or receive such refund for the benefit of such person or his`
  line estate.
  line
  line `(3) No claim for refund under sub-section (1) shall be allowed unless it is made within a period of`
  line `twelve months from the date of the order giving rise to a claim for such refund, and the`
  line `Commissioner shall, except as otherwise provided in this Act, refund any amount which becomes due to a`
  line `dealer in the prescribed manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may allow a claim for refund to be made after the expiry of the said`
  line `period but not later than twelve months from such expiry, if he is satisfied that there was sufficient cause`
  line `for not making such claim within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an amount required to be refunded by the Commissioner to any person as a result of`
  line `any order passed in appeal or other proceedings under this Act is not so refunded to him within ninety`
  line `days from the date of his claim under sub-section (3), such person shall be entitled to be paid simple`
  line `interest on such amount at one per cent. per month from the date immediately following the expiry of the`
  line `period of ninety days for a period of one month and at one and a half per cent. per month, thereafter for so`
  line `long as the refund is not made.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- If the delay in making the refund during any of the periods referred to in`
  line `this sub-section is attributable to the person making the claim, whether wholly or in part, the period of the`
  line `delay attributable to him shall be excluded from the period for which interest is payable.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any question arises as to the period to be excluded for the purposes of calculation of`
  line `interest under sub-section (4), such question shall be determined by the Commissioner whose decision`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an order giving rise to a refund is the subject matter of an appeal or further proceeding or`
  line `where any other proceeding under this Act is pending and the Commissioner is of opinion that the grant`
  line `of the refund is likely to adversely affect the revenue, the Commissioner may withhold the refund till such`
  line `time as the Commissioner may determine.`
  line
  line `(7) In any claim for refund, it shall not be open to the dealer to question the correctness of any`
  line `assessment or other matter decided which has become final and conclusive or ask for a review of the same`
  line `and the dealer shall not be entitled to any relief on such claim except refund of tax wrongly paid or paid in`
  line excess.
  line
  line `(8) Any tax levied and collected under this Act in respect of sale in Delhi of any declared goods`
  line `which are subsequently sold in the course of inter-State trade or commerce, shall be reimbursed to the`
  line `person making the sale on the course of inter-State trade or commerce, in such manner and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of sub-section (8), "declared goods" means goods declared by`
  line `section 14 of the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956) to be of special importance in inter-State trade`
  line `or commerce.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (33141)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Set-off.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33141&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Commissioner is satisfied that delay beyond the prescribed period has`
  line `occurred in the grant of a certificate of registration to a dealer and that such delay was not wholly due to`
  line `any fault, omission or negligence on the part of the dealer, the amount of tax, if any, paid on sales of`
  line `goods made to such dealer which would not have been payable but for the delay in the grant of a`
  line `certificate of registration as aforesaid, shall be adjusted against any amount payable by the dealer under`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) in case the amount of tax so paid by the dealer exceeds his liability to pay any amount under`
  line `this Act, the adjustment shall be made to the extent of such liability and the balance shall be refunded`
  line `to the dealer; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case there is no liability to pay any amount under this Act, the entire amount of tax`
  line `paid shall be refunded to the dealer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the dealer shall not be entitled to any such adjustment or refund in respect of the`
  line `goods which are not specified in the certificate of registration granted to him.`
  line
  line `(2) No application for adjustment or refund of tax under this section shall be entertained unless it is`
  line `made within three months from the date on which a certificate of registration is granted to the dealer.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (33142)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Liability in case of transfer of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33142&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a dealer, liable to pay tax under this Act,`
  line `transfers his business in whole or in part, by sale, gift, lease, leave or licence, hire or in any other manner`
  line `whatsoever, the dealer and the person to whom the business is so transferred shall jointly and severally be`
  line `liable to pay the tax (including any penalty) due from the dealer up to the time of such transfer, whether`
  line `such tax (including any penalty) has been assessed before such transfer, but has remained unpaid or is`
  line `assessed thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the transferee or the lessee of a business referred to in sub-section (1) carries on such`
  line `business either in his own name or in some other name, he shall be liable to pay tax on the sale of goods`
  line `effected by him with effect from the date of such transfer and shall, if he is an existing dealer, apply`
  line `within the prescribed time for amendment of his certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (33143)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Liability in case of company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33143&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person--`
  line
  line `(a) who is a liquidator of any company which is being wound up whether under the orders of a`
  line `court or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(b) who has been appointed the receiver of any assets of a company (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"liquidator"),`
  line
  line `shall, within thirty days after he has become such liquidator, give notice of his appointment as such to the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall, after making such inquiries or calling for such information as he may`
  line `deem fit, notify the liquidator within three months from the date on which he received notice of the`
  line `appointment of the liquidator, the amount which, in the opinion of the Commissioner, would be sufficient`
  line `to provide for any tax (including any penalty) which is then, or is likely thereafter to become, payable by`
  line `the company.`
  line
  line `(3) The liquidator shall not part with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hand`
  line `until he has been notified by the Commissioner under sub-section (2) and on being so notified, the`
  line `liquidator shall set aside an amount equal to the amount notified and, until he so sets aside such amount,`
  line `he shall not part with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hand:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall debar the liquidator from parting with such`
  line `assets or properties in compliance with any order of a court or for the purpose of the payment of the tax`
  line `and penalty, if any, payable by the company under this Act or for making any payment to secured`
  line `creditors whose debts are entitled under law to priority of payment over debts due to Government on the`
  line `date of liquidation or for meeting such costs and expenses of the winding up of the company as are in the`
  line `opinion of the Commissioner reasonable.`
  line
  line `(4) If the liquidator fails to give notice in accordance with sub-section (1) or fails to set aside the`
  line `amount as required by sub-section (3) or parts with any assets of the company or the properties in his`
  line `hand in contravention of the provisions of that sub-section, he shall be personally liable for the payment`
  line `of the tax and penalty, if any, which the company would be liable to pay under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the amount of any tax and penalty, if any, payable by the company is notified`
  line `under sub-section (2), the personal liability of the liquidator under this sub-section shall be to the extent of`
  line `such amount.`
  line
  line `(5) Where there are more liquidators than one, the obligations and liabilities attached to the liquidator`
  line `under this section shall attach to all the liquidators jointly and severally.`
  line
  line `(6) When any private company is wound up and any tax and penalty, if any, assessed under this Act`
  line `on the company for any period, whether before or in the course of or after its liquidation, cannot be`
  line `recovered, then every person who was director of the private company at any time during the period for`
  line `which the tax is due, shall be jointly and severally liable for the payment of such tax and penalty, if any,`
  line `unless he proves to the satisfaction of the Commissioner that non-recovery cannot be attributed to any`
  line `gross neglect, misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the company.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(8) For the purposes of this section, the expressions company and private company shall have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them under clauses (i) and (iii) of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (33144)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Liability of partners of firm to pay tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33144&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, where`
  line `any firm is liable to pay any tax (including any penalty) under this Act, the firm and each of the partners`
  line `of the firm shall be jointly and severally liable for such payment:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such partner retires from the firm, he shall intimate the date of his retirement`
  line `to the Commissioner by a notice in that behalf in writing and he shall be liable to pay tax (including any`
  line `penalty) remaining unpaid at the time of his retirement and any tax (including any penalty) due up to the`
  line `date of his retirement though unassessed on that date:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if no such intimation is given within fifteen days from the date of retirement, the`
  line `liability of the partner under the first proviso shall continue until the date on which such intimation is`
  line `received by the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (33145)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Liability of guardians, trustees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33145&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Where the business in respect of which tax is payable`
  line `under this Act is carried on by, or is in the charge of any guardian, trustee or agent of a minor`
  line `or other incapacitated person on his behalf and for the benefit of such minor or other incapacitated person,`
  line `the tax (including any penalty) shall be levied upon and recoverable from such guardian, trustee or agent,`
  line `as the case may be, in like manner and to the same extent as it would be assessed upon and recoverable`
  line `from any such minor or other incapacitated person, if he were of full age and of sound mind and if he`
  line `were conducting the business himself, and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (33146)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Liability of Court of Wards, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33146&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where the estate or any portion of the estate of a dealer`
  line `owning a business in respect of which tax is payable under this Act is under the control of the Court of`
  line `Wards, the Administrator-General, the Official Trustee or any receiver or manager (including any person,`
  line `whatever be his designation, who in fact manages the business) appointed by or under any order of a`
  line `court, the tax (including any penalty) shall be levied upon and be recoverable from such Court of Wards,`
  line `Administrator-General, Official Trustee, receiver or manager in like manner and to the same extent as it`
  line `would be assessable upon and be recoverable from the dealer if he were conducting the business himself;`
  line `and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (33147)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Liability in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33147&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a dealer is a firm or an association of persons or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family, and such firm, association or family has discontinued business--`
  line
  line `(a) the tax payable under this Act, by such firm, association or family up to the date of such`
  line `discontinuance may be assessed as if no such discontinuance had taken place; and`
  line
  line `(b) every person who was at the time of such discontinuance a partner of such firm, or a member`
  line `of such association or family, shall, notwithstanding such discontinuance, be liable jointly and`
  line `severally for the payment of tax assessed and penalty imposed and payable by such firm, association`
  line `or family, whether such tax (including any penalty) has been assessed prior to or after such`
  line `discontinuance, and subject as aforesaid, the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply as if`
  line `every such person or partner or member were himself a dealer:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the partner of a firm liable to pay such tax (including any penalty) dies, the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (4) shall, so far as may be, apply.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a change has occurred in the constitution of a firm or association, the partners or members`
  line `of the firm or association as it existed before and as it exists after its re-constitution, shall, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of section 34, jointly and severally be liable to pay any tax (including any`
  line `penalty) due from such firm or association for any period before its re-constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply where the dealer, being a firm or`
  line `association of persons, is dissolved or where the dealer, being a Hindu undivided family, has effected`
  line `partition with respect to the business carried on by it and accordingly references in that sub-section to`
  line `discontinuance shall be construed as references to dissolution or, as the case may, to partition.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a dealer liable to pay tax under this Act dies, than--`
  line
  line `(a) if the business carried on by the dealer is continued after his death by his legal representative`
  line `or any other person, such legal representative or other person, shall be liable to pay the tax (including`
  line `any penalty) due from the dealer under this Act, whether such tax (including any penalty) has been`
  line `assessed before his death but has remained unpaid, or is assessed after his death;`
  line
  line `(b) if the business carried on by the dealer is discontinued after his death, his legal`
  line `representative shall be liable to pay out of the estate of the deceased, to the extent the estate is capable`
  line `of meeting the charge, the tax (including any penalty) due from the dealer under this Act, whether`
  line `such tax (including any penalty) has been assessed before his death but has remained unpaid, or is`
  line `assessed after his death,`
  line
  line `and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply to such legal representative or other person as`
  line `if he were the dealer himself.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section and section 40, "legal representative" has`
  line `the meaning assigned to it in clause (11) of section 2 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (33148)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title Accounts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33148&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every dealer liable to pay tax under this Act, and every other dealer on whom a`
  line `notice has been served to furnish returns under sub-section (2) of section 21 shall keep at his place of`
  line `business a true account of the value of goods bought and sold by him, and if the Commissioner considers`
  line `that such account is not sufficiently clear and intelligible to enable him to make a proper check of the`
  line `returns referred to in that sub-section, he may require such dealer by notice in writing to keep such`
  line `accounts (including records of purchases and sales) and as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct any class of registered`
  line `dealers generally to keep such accounts (including records of purchases and sales) as may be specified in`
  line `the notification subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (33149)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Memoranda of sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33149&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `If a registered dealer--`
  line
  line `(a) sells goods to another registered dealer, or`
  line
  line `(b) makes sales in the course of inter-State trade or commerce, or`
  line
  line `(c) sells any goods exceeding ten rupees in value in any one transaction to any other person,`
  line
  line `he shall issue to the purchaser a bill or cash memorandum serially numbered, signed and dated by him`
  line `or his servant, manager or agent and showing therein his name and address and such other particulars as`
  line `may be prescribed and he shall keep a duplicate or copy of such bill or cash memorandum duly signed`
  line `and dated and preserve it for a period of not less than five years from the end of the year unless any`
  line `proceedings in respect of that year are pending in which case they shall be preserved till the final decision`
  line `in those proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in respect of any goods or class of goods or any dealers or class of dealers,`
  line `the Administrator is of the opinion that it is not practicable to issue any bills or cash memoranda for sale`
  line `of goods exceeding ten rupees in value in any one transaction to any other person, he may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(i) specify such amount exceeding ten rupees in value as the amount for the issue of such bills or`
  line `cash memoranda;`
  line
  line `(ii) exempt such goods or class of goods or dealers or class of dealers from the operation of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (33150)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Information to be furnished regarding change of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33150&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `If any dealer to whom the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 21 apply--`
  line
  line `(a) sells or otherwise disposes of his business or any part of his business or any place of business,`
  line `or effects or comes to know of any other change in the ownership of the business; or`
  line
  line `(b) discontinues his business or changes his place of business or warehouse, or opens a new place`
  line `of business; or`
  line
  line `(c) changes the name or nature of his business, or effects any change in the goods or class of`
  line `goods in which he carries on his business and which is or are specified in his certificate of`
  line `registration; or`
  line
  line `(d) enters into partnership or other association in regard to his business,`
  line
  line `he shall, within the prescribed time, inform the prescribed authority accordingly, and if any such dealer`
  line `dies, his legal representative shall in like manner inform the said authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (33151)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Production and inspection of accounts and documents and search of premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33151&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commissioner may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, require any dealer--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce before him such books of accounts, registers or documents,`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish such information relating to the stock of goods of, or purchases, sales or deliveries`
  line `of goods by, the dealer or any other information relating to his business,`
  line
  line `as may be deemed necessary, for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) All books of accounts, registers and documents relating to the stock of goods of, or purchases,`
  line `sales and deliveries of goods by, any dealer, and`
  line
  line `(b) All goods kept in any place of business or warehouse of any dealer,`
  line
  line `shall at all reasonable times be open to inspection by the Commissioner and the Commissioner may take`
  line `or cause to be taken such copies or extracts of the said books of accounts, registers or documents and such`
  line `inventory of the goods found as appear to him necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Commissioner, upon information in his possession or otherwise, has reasonable`
  line `grounds to believe that--`
  line
  line `(a) any person to whom a notice under this Act was issued to produce, or cause to be produced,`
  line `any books of accounts or other documents has omitted or failed to produce or caused to be produced`
  line `such books of accounts or other documents, as required by such notice, or`
  line
  line `(b) any person to whom a notice as aforesaid has been or might be issued, will not, or`
  line `would not produce or cause to be produced any books of accounts or other documents which`
  line `will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceedings under the Bengal Finance (Sales Tax)`
  line `Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as it was in force in Delhi, or under this Act,`
  line
  line `(c) books of accounts, registers or documents of any dealer may be destroyed, mutilated,`
  line `altered, falsified or secreted or any sales by that dealer have been or may be suppressed, with a`
  line `view to evade or attempt to evade payment of tax due under the Bengal Finance`
  line `(Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as it was in force in Delhi, or under this Act,the Commissioner or any other person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9, if so authorised by`
  line `the Commissioner may, --`
  line
  line `(i) enter and search any building or place where he has reason to suspect that books of accounts`
  line `and other documents or the sale proceeds are kept;`
  line
  line `(ii) break open the lock of any door, box, locker, safe, almirah or other receptacle for exercising`
  line `the powers conferred by clause (i) where the keys thereof are not available;`
  line
  line `(iii) seize any such books of accounts or other documents or any inventory of goods as appear to`
  line `him necessary for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(iv) place marks of identification on any books of accounts or other documents or make or cause`
  line `to be made extracts or copies therefrom;`
  line
  line `(v) make a note or any inventory of any such money or goods found as a result of such search;`
  line
  line `(vi) seal the premises including the office, shop, godown, box, locker, safe, almirah`
  line `or other receptacle if the owner or the person in occupation or in charge of such office, shop, godown,`
  line `box, locker, safe, almirah or other receptacle leaves the place or is not available or fails or refuses to`
  line `open it when called upon to do so.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner may requisition the services of any police officer or any public servant, or of`
  line `both to assist him for all or any of the purposes specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Commissioner seizes any books of accounts or other documents, he shall give the`
  line `dealer or the person present on his behalf, as the case may be, a receipt for the same and obtain`
  line `acknowledgement of the receipt so given to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the dealer or person from whose custody the books of accounts`
  line `or other documents are seized refuses to give an acknowledgement, the Commissioner may leave the`
  line `receipt at the premises and record this fact:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the dealer or person aforesaid may file objections before the Commissioner`
  line `against such search, seizure or inventory within seven days of such search seizure or inventory.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner shall keep in his custody the books of accounts, registers or documents seized`
  line `under sub-section (3) for such period not later than the completion of all the proceedings under this Act in`
  line `respect of years for which those books of accounts, registers or documents are relevant, as he considers`
  line `necessary, and thereafter shall return the same to the dealer or any other person from whose custody or`
  line `power they were seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may, before returning such books of accounts or other documents as`
  line `aforesaid, place or cause to be placed such marks of identification thereon as appear to him to be`
  line `necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Commissioner may, before returning the books of accounts`
  line `and other documents, require that the dealer or the person, as the case may be, shall give a written`
  line `undertaking that the books of accounts and other documents shall be presented whenever required by any`
  line `competent authority for any proceedings under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) Save as otherwise provided in this section, every search or seizure made under this`
  line `section shall be carried on in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches or seizures made under that Code.`
  line
  line `(8) The Commissioner may, for the purposes of this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) require any person, including a banking company, post office or any officer thereof, to furnish`
  line `information in relation to such points or matters or to furnish statements of accounts and affairs`
  line `verified in the manner specified by him, giving information in relation to such points or matters as`
  line `in his opinion will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) require any person--`
  line
  line `(i) who transports or holds in custody, for delivery to or on behalf of any dealer any goods to`
  line `give any information likely to be in his possession in respect of such goods or to permit`
  line `inspection thereof, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(ii) who maintains or has in his possession any books of accounts, registers or documents`
  line `relating to the business of a dealer to produce such books of accounts, registers or documents for`
  line inspection.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (33152)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Commissioner and other authorities to take evidence on oath, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33152&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commissioner or any person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath or affirmation;`
  line
  line `(b) compelling the production of accounts and documents; and`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses,`
  line
  line `and any proceeding under this Act before the Commissioner or any person appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rule made in this behalf, any authority referred to in sub-section (1) may impound`
  line `and retain in its custody for such period as it thinks fit, any books of accounts or other documents`
  line `produced before it in any proceedings under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist the Commissioner shall`
  line not--
  line
  line `(a) impound any books of accounts or other documents without recording his reasons for so`
  line `doing; or`
  line
  line `(b) retain in his custody any such books or documents for a period exceeding thirty days,`
  line
  line `without obtaining the approval of the Commissioner therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (33153)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33153&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any order, not being an order mentioned in`
  line `section 44 passed under this Act or the rules made thereunder, may appeal to the prescribed authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an order, not being an order mentioned in section 44 or made under section 47 is`
  line `passed by the Commissioner, the person aggrieved may appeal therefrom to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner or any person aggrieved by an order passed in appeal by the prescribed`
  line `authority may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 62, no appeal shall be entertained unless it is filed within sixty`
  line `days from the date of service of the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal filed under this section shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and in the case of an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal filed by any person other than`
  line `the Commissioner, shall be accompanied by a fee of fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) No appeal against an order of assessment with or without penalty or against an order imposing the`
  line `penalty shall be entertained by an appellate authority unless such appeal is accompanied by a satisfactory`
  line `proof of the payment of tax with or without penalty or, as the case may be, of the payment of the penalty`
  line `in respect of which the appeal has been preferred:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may, if it thinks fit, for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `entertain an appeal against such order--`
  line
  line `(a) without payment of the tax and penalty, if any, or as the case may be, of the penalty, on the`
  line `appellant furnishing in the prescribed manner security for such amount as it may direct, or`
  line
  line `(b) on proof of payment of such smaller sum, with or without security for such amount of tax or`
  line `penalty which remains unpaid, as it may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal shall be entertained by the appellate authority unless it is satisfied that`
  line `such amount of tax as the appellant may admit to be due from him has been paid.`
  line
  line `(6) The appellate authority may, after giving the appellant an opportunity of being heard,--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the assessment (including any penalty imposed), or`
  line
  line `(b) set aside the assessment (including any penalty imposed) and direct the assessing authority to`
  line `make a fresh assessment after such further inquiry as may be directed, or`
  line
  line `(c) pass such order as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(7) Save as provided in section 45, an order passed by Appellate Tribunal on appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (33154)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Non-appealable orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33154&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No appeal and no application for revision shall lie against--`
  line
  line `(a) a notice issued under this Act calling upon a dealer for assessment or asking a dealer to show`
  line `cause as to why he should not be prosecuted for an offence under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) an order pertaining to the seizure or retention of books of accounts, register`
  line `and other documents; or`
  line
  line `(c) an order sanctioning prosecution under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) an interim order passed in the course of any proceedings under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (33155)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Statement of case to the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33155&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within sixty days from the date of an order passed by`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (6) of section 43, the dealer or the Commissioner may, by`
  line `application in writing, and accompanied, where the application is made by a dealer, by a fee of fifty`
  line `rupees, require the Appellate Tribunal to refer to the High Court any question of law arising out of such`
  line `order, and, subject to the other provisions contained in this section, the Appellate Tribunal shall, within`
  line `one hundred and twenty days of the receipt of such application, draw up a statement of the case and refer`
  line `it to the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the dealer or the Commissioner was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from presenting the application within the period here in before specified,`
  line `allow it to be presented within a further period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Appellate Tribunal refuses to state the case which it has been required to do, on the ground`
  line `that no question of law arises, the dealer or the Commissioner, as the case may be, within thirty days of`
  line `the communication of such refusal either withdraw his application (and if he does so, any fee paid shall be`
  line `refunded), or apply to the High Court against such refusal.`
  line
  line `(3) If upon receipt of an application under sub-section (2), the High Court is not satisfied as to the`
  line `correctness of the decision of the Appellate Tribunal, it may require the Appellate Tribunal to state the`
  line `case and refer it, and on receipt of such requisition, the Appellate Tribunal shall state the case and refer it`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) If the High Court is not satisfied that the statement in a case referred to it are sufficient to enable it`
  line `to determine the questions raised thereby, the Court may refer the case back to the Appellate Tribunal for`
  line `the purpose of making such additions thereto or alternations therein as it may direct in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The High Court upon the hearing of any such case shall decide the question of law raised thereby,`
  line `and shall deliver its judgment thereon containing the grounds on which such decision is founded,`
  line `and shall send to the Appellate Tribunal a copy of such judgment under the seal of the Court and the`
  line `signature of the Registrar, and the Appellate Tribunal shall dispose of the case accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a reference is made to the High Court under this section, the costs which shall not include`
  line `the fee referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in the discretion of the Court.`
  line
  line `(7) The payment of the amount of tax and penalty (if any) due in accordance with the order of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal in respect of which an application has been made under sub-section (1) shall not be`
  line `stayed pending the disposal of such application or any reference made in consequence thereof but if such`
  line `amount is reduced as a result of such reference, the excess tax paid shall be refunded in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (33156)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Revision of orders prejudicial to revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33156&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may call for and examine the`
  line `records of any proceeding under this Act and if he considers that any order passed therein by any person`
  line `appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him, is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of revenue, he may, after giving the dealer an opportunity of being heard and after making or`
  line `causing to be made such inquiry as he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances of`
  line `the case justify, including an order enhancing or modifying the assessment and penalty (if any) imposed`
  line `or cancelling the assessment and penalty (if any) imposed and directing a fresh assessment:`
  line
  line `Provided that a final order under this section shall be made before the expiry of five years from the`
  line `date of the order sought to be revised.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (33157)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Revision of other orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33157&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any order, other than an order referred to in`
  line `section 44 or to which section 46 applies, passed by a person appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9 to assist him, the Commissioner may, either on his own motion or on an application filed in`
  line `accordance with such rules as may be prescribed, call for the record of any proceeding under this Act in`
  line `which any such order has been passed and may make such inquiry or cause such inquiry to be made`
  line `and, subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such orders thereon, not being an order prejudicial to`
  line `the dealer, as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not revise any order under this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) where an appeal against the order is pending before the appellate authority under`
  line `section 43; or`
  line
  line `(b) where, if such appeal lies, the time within which it may be filed has not expired, or`
  line
  line `(c) where in the case of the second appeal, the dealer has not waived his right of appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall not on his own motion revise any order under this section after the expiry`
  line `of two years from the date of the order sought to be revised.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an application for revision under this section by the dealer, the application shall be`
  line `made within two years from the date on which the order in question was communicated to him or the date`
  line `on which he otherwise comes to know of it, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (33158)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33158&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner or any person appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him, may at any time within two years from the date`
  line `of any order passed by the Commissioner or by that person, as the case may be, on his own motion,`
  line `rectify any mistake apparent from the record, and shall within a like period, rectify any such mistake`
  line `which has been brought to his notice by any person affected by such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rectification shall be made, if it has the effect of enhancing the tax or reducing`
  line `the amount of refund, unless the Commissioner or the person appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9 to assist him, as the case may be, has given notice in writing to the person likely to be affected`
  line `by the order of his intention to do so and has allowed such person a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line heard.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply to the rectification of a mistake by an appellate`
  line `authority under section 43 as they apply to the rectification of a mistake by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any matter has been considered and decided in any proceeding by way of appeal or`
  line `revision relating to an order referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the authority passing`
  line `such order may, notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, amend`
  line `the order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, in relation to any matter other than`
  line `the matter which has been so considered and decided.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any such rectification has the effect of reducing the amount of the tax or penalty, the`
  line `Commissioner shall, in the prescribed manner, refund any amount due to such person.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any such rectification has the effect of enhancing the amount of the tax or penalty or`
  line `reducing the amount of the refund, the Commissioner shall recover the amount due from such person in`
  line `the manner provided for in Chapter V.`
  line
  line `(6) Save as provided in the foregoing sub-sections, and subject to such rules as may be prescribed,`
  line `any assessment made or order passed under this Act or the rules made thereunder by any person`
  line `appointed under section 9 or by the Appellate Tribunal may be reviewed by such person or by the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, suo motu or upon an application made in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(7) Before any order is passed under sub-section (6) which is likely to affect any person adversely,`
  line `such person shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (33159)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Determination of disputed questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33159&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any question arises, otherwise than in proceedings`
  line `before a court, or before the Commissioner has commenced assessment or reassessment of a dealer under`
  line `section 23 or 24, whether for the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any person, society, club or association or any firm or any branch or department of any firm is`
  line `a dealer; or`
  line
  line `(b) any particular thing done to any goods amounts to or results in the manufacture of goods`
  line `within the meaning of that term as given in clause (h) of section 2; or`
  line
  line `(c) any transaction is a sale, and if so, the sale price therefor; or`
  line
  line `(d) any particular dealer is required to be registered; or`
  line
  line `(e) any tax is payable in respect of any particular sale, or if the tax is payable, the rate thereof,`
  line `the Commissioner shall, within such period as may be prescribed, make an order determining such`
  line question.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the Commissioner shall be deemed to have`
  line `commenced assessment or reassessment of a dealer under section 23 or section 24, when the dealer is`
  line `served with any notice by the Commissioner under section 23 or section 24 as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may direct that the determination shall not affect the liability of any person`
  line `under this Act as respects any sale effected prior to the determination.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such question arises from any order already passed under this Act or under the Bengal`
  line `Finance (Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as then in force in Delhi, no such question shall`
  line `be entertained for determination under this section; but such question may be raised in appeal against, or`
  line `by way of revision of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (33160)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33160&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) holds, gives, produces or accepts a declaration under the second proviso to clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 4, or under the first proviso to section 5, which he knows or has reason to`
  line `believe to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) carries on business as a dealer without obtaining a certificate of registration as required`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 14 or sub-section (1) of section 17; or`
  line
  line `(c) not being a registered dealer, represents when purchasing goods that he is a registered`
  line `dealer or;`
  line
  line `(d) being a registered dealer, represents when purchasing any goods or class of goods not covered`
  line `by his certificate of registration, that such goods or class of goods are covered by such certificate; or`
  line
  line `(e) fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (5) of section 20; or`
  line
  line `(f) fails to submit any return as required by sub-section (2) of section 21 by the prescribed date`
  line `or submits a false return; or`
  line
  line `(g) not being a registered dealer, collects any amount by way of tax under this Act or make any`
  line `collection of such tax otherwise than in accordance with this Act or the rules made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(h) fails to keep a true account of the value of goods bought or sold by him as required by`
  line `section 38, or fails when required so to do under that section, to keep any account or record of`
  line `purchases or sales specified in any notice or notification referred to in that section; or`
  line
  line `(i) fails or neglects to issue cash memorandum or bills as required under section 39; or`
  line
  line `(j) knowingly maintains or produces incorrect accounts, registers or documents or knowingly`
  line `furnishes incorrect information; or`
  line
  line `(k) neglects to furnish any information required by section 40; or`
  line
  line `(l) refuses to comply with any requirements made of him under section 41; or`
  line
  line `(m) closes his place of business with a view to preventing inspection under section 41; or`
  line
  line `(n) obstructs or prevents any officer making inspection, search or seizure under section 41, or`
  line `performing any functions under section 64, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(o) being the owner or person in charge of a goods vehicle fails, neglects or refuses to comply`
  line `with any of the requirements contained in section 64; or`
  line
  line `(p) aids or abets any person in the commission of any offence specified in clauses (a) to (o),`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine,`
  line `or with both, and where the offence is a continuing one, with a daily fine not exceeding two hundred`
  line `rupees during the period of the continuance of the offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that no prosecution for an offence under this Act shall be instituted in respect of the same`
  line `facts in respect of which a penalty has been imposed under sub-section (6) of section 20, sub-section (6)`
  line `of section 23, section 55, section 56 or section 57:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person shall not be deemed to have committed an offence under clause (b) if`
  line `he had applied for registration under this Act in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14, or sub-section (2) of section 17, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if any person commits an offence under`
  line `clause (a) or clause (f) or clause (j) or clause (l) or clause (m) or clause (o) of that sub-section and the`
  line `court is satisfied that the offence has been committed wilfully, he shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and with fine, and where the offence is a`
  line `continuing one, with a daily fine not exceeding three hundred rupees during the period of the continuance`
  line `of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (33161)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33161&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (33162)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33162&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act or`
  line `rules made thereunder except with the previous sanction of the Commissioner, and no court inferior to`
  line `that of a Metropolitan Magistrate shall try any such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all`
  line `offences punishable under this Act or rules made thereunder shall be cognizable and bailable.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (33163)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Investigation of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33163&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, the`
  line `Commissioner may authorise either generally or in respect of a particular case or class of cases any`
  line `person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him to investigate all or any of the offences`
  line `punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person so authorised shall, in the conduct of such investigation exercise the powers`
  line `conferred by the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), upon an officer in charge of a police`
  line `station for the investigation of a cognizable offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (33164)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33164&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, the`
  line `Commissioner may accept, from any person alleged to have committed an offence under section 50 or`
  line `under any rules made under this Act, either before or after the commencement of any proceedings against`
  line `such person in respect of such offence, by way of composition for such offence, a sum not exceeding`
  line `five thousand rupees or where the offence alleged to have been committed is under any of the`
  line `clauses (a), (b), (c), (d) and (f) of that section, not exceeding three times the amount of the tax which`
  line `would thereby have been avoided, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(2) On payment in full of such sum as may be determined by the Commissioner`
  line `under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) no proceedings shall be commenced against such person as aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `(b) if any proceedings have already been commenced against such person as aforesaid, such`
  line `proceedings shall not be further proceeded with.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (33165)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Imposition of Penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33165&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a dealer fails without reasonable cause to furnish any return by the`
  line `prescribed date as required under sub-section (2) of section 21, or to pay the tax due according to the`
  line `return as required by sub-section (3) of that section, the Commissioner may after giving the dealer an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, direct that the dealer shall pay, by way of penalty, in addition to the amount of`
  line `tax payable, a sum not exceeding twice that amount or where no tax is payable a sum not exceeding two`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The penalties specified under sub-section (1) may be imposed by the Commissioner`
  line `notwithstanding the fact that assessment proceedings have not been initiated against the dealer under`
  line `section 23.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (33166)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Penalty for concealment of sales or furnishing inaccurate particulars or making false representations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33166&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner or any person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to`
  line `assist him, in the course of any proceedings under this Act, is satisfied that a dealer has concealed the`
  line `particulars of his sales or has furnished inaccurate particulars of his sales, he may, after giving the dealer a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, direct that the dealer shall pay, by way of penalty, in addition to the amount of tax payable, a sum not exceeding two and a half times the amount of tax which would`
  line `thereby have been avoided.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person commits an offence under clause (a) of section 50, the Commissioner or any person`
  line `appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him may, after giving that person a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, impose upon such person by way of penalty, a sum not`
  line `exceeding two and a half times the amount of tax which would thereby have been avoided.`
  line
  line `(3) If a person purchasing goods commits an offence under clause (c) or clause (d) of section 50, the`
  line `authority which granted him, or, as the case may be, is competent to grant him a certificate of registration`
  line `under this Act, may, after giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard by order in writing impose`
  line `upon him by way of penalty, a sum not exceeding two and a half times the tax which could have been`
  line `levied under this Act in respect of the sale to him of the goods, if the offence had not been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (33167)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Penalty for contravening provisions regarding collection of tax by dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33167&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `acts in contravention of the provisions of section 22, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding two and`
  line `a half times the tax wrongly collected:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not impose such penalty unless the person concerned has been`
  line `given an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (33168)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Service of notice when family is disrupted or firm is dissolved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33168&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Hindu undivided`
  line `family has been partitioned, notices under this Act may be served on the person who was the last manager`
  line `of the Hindu family, or if such person cannot be found, then on all adults who were members of the Hindu`
  line `family, immediately before the partition.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a firm or an association of persons is dissolved, notices under this Act may be served on`
  line `any person who was a partner (not being a minor) of the firm, or member of the association, as the case`
  line `may be, immediately before its dissolution.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (33169)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Service of notice in the case of discontinued business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33169&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where an assessment is to be made in`
  line `respect of business which has been discontinued, a notice under this Act shall be served in the case of a`
  line `firm or an association of persons on any person who was a member of such firm or association at the time`
  line `of its discontinuance or in the case of a company on the principal officer thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (33170)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Appearance before any authority in proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33170&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who is entitled or required`
  line `to attend before any authority in connection with any proceedings under this Act, may attend,--`
  line
  line `(a) by a person authorised by him in writing in this behalf, being a relative or a person regularly`
  line `employed by him; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a legal practitioner or chartered accountant who is not disqualified by or under`
  line `sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(c) by a sales tax practitioner who possesses the prescribed qualifications and is entered in the list`
  line `which the Commissioner shall maintain in that behalf, and who is not disqualified by or under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, by order in writing and for reasons to be recorded therein, disqualify for`
  line `such period as is stated in the order from attending before any such authority any legal practitioner,`
  line `chartered accountant or sales tax practitioner--`
  line
  line `(i) who has been removed or dismissed from Government service; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who being a legal practitioner or chartered accountant is found guilty of misconduct in`
  line `connection with any proceedings under this Act by an authority empowered to take disciplinary`
  line `action against the members of the profession to which he belongs; or`
  line
  line `(iii) who being a sales tax practitioner is found guilty of such misconduct by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) No order of disqualification shall be made in respect of any particular person unless he has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person against whom any order of disqualification is made under this section may, within one`
  line `month of the date of communication of such order, appeal to the Administrator to have the order`
  line cancelled.
  line
  line `(5) The order of the Commissioner shall not take effect until one month of the making thereof or`
  line `when an appeal is preferred, until the appeal is decided.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner may at any time suo motu or on an application made to him in this behalf,`
  line `revoke any order made against any person under sub-section (2) and thereupon such person shall cease to`
  line `be disqualified.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (33171)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Change of an incumbent of an office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33171&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Whenever in respect of any proceeding under this Act`
  line `the Commissioner or any person appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him, ceases to`
  line `exercise jurisdiction and is succeeded by another who has and exercises jurisdiction, the person so`
  line `succeeding may continue the proceeding from the stage at which the proceeding was left by his`
  line `predecessor:`
  line
  line `Provided that the dealer concerned may demand that before the proceeding is so continued, the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that before any order of assessment is passed`
  line `against him, he be re-heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (33172)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Extension of period of limitation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33172&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Appellate authority may admit an`
  line `appeal under section 43 after the period of limitation laid down in that section, if the appellant satisfies`
  line `the appellate authority that he has sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within such period.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the period laid down under sections 43, 45, 46 and 47, the provisions of`
  line `sections 4 and 12 of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, so far as may be, apply.`
  line
  line `(3) In computing the period of limitation prescribed by or under any provision of this Act, or the rules`
  line `made thereunder, other than section 43, 45, 46 or 47, any period during which any proceeding is stayed by`
  line `an order or injunction of any court shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (33173)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Returns, etc., to be confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33173&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) All particulars contained in any statement made, return`
  line `furnished or accounts or documents produced in accordance with this Act, or in any record of evidence`
  line `given in the course of any proceedings under this Act, other than proceedings before a criminal`
  line `court, shall, save as provided in sub-section (3), be treated as confidential, and notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), no court shall, save as aforesaid, be entitled to`
  line `require any servant of the Government to produce before it any such statement, return, account, document`
  line `or record or any part thereof, or to give evidence before it in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If, save as provided in sub-section (3), any servant of the Government discloses any of the`
  line `particulars referred to in sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to`
  line `six months, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to the disclosure--`
  line
  line `(a) of any of the particulars referred to in sub-section (1) for the purposes of investigation or`
  line `prosecution under this Act or the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other enactment for the time`
  line `being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) of such facts to an officer of the Central Government or any State Government as may be`
  line `necessary for verification of such facts or for the purposes of enabling that Government to levy or`
  line `realise any tax imposed by it; or`
  line
  line `(c) of any such particulars where such disclosure is occasioned by the lawful employment under`
  line `this Act of any process for the service of any notice or the recovery of any demand; or`
  line
  line `(d) of any such particulars to a civil court in any suit or proceeding to which the Government or`
  line `any sales tax authority is a party and which relates to any matter arising out of any proceeding under`
  line `this Act or under any other law for the time being in force authorizing any sales tax authority to`
  line `exercise any powers thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(e) of any such particulars by any public servant where the disclosure is occasioned by the lawful`
  line `exercise by him of his powers under the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), to impound an`
  line `insufficiently stamped document; or`
  line
  line `(f) of any such particulars to the Reserve Bank of India as are required by that Bank to enable it to`
  line `compile financial statistics of international investment and balance of payment; or`
  line
  line `(g) of any such particulars to any officer appointed by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India for purpose of audit of tax receipts or refunds; or`
  line
  line `(h) of any such particulars relevant to any inquiry into a charge of misconduct in connection with`
  line `income-tax proceedings against a legal practitioner or chartered accountant, to the authority`
  line `empowered to take disciplinary action against members of the profession to which he belongs; or`
  line
  line `(i) of such particulars to the officers of the Central Government or any State Government for`
  line `such other purposes, as the Administrator may by general or special order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (33174)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Setting up of check-posts and barriers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33174&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, set up check-posts or barriers, or both, at any place in Delhi with a view to preventing`
  line `evasion of tax and other dues payable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner or person in charge of a goods vehicle shall carry with him a goods vehicle record, a`
  line `trip sheet or a log book, as the case may be, and a bill of sale or a delivery note containing such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed in respect of the goods carried in the goods vehicle and produce the same`
  line `before any officer in charge of a check-post or barrier or any other officer as may be empowered by the`
  line `Administrator in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or person in charge of a goods vehicle entering or leaving Delhi shall also file a`
  line `declaration containing such particulars in the prescribed form obtainable from the prescribed authority`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed, before the officer in charge of a check-post or barrier or before`
  line `the other officer empowered as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner or person in charge of a goods vehicle after filing a declaration at the`
  line `time of entering Delhi that the goods are meant to be carried to a place outside Delhi, fails, without`
  line `reasonable cause, to carry such goods outside Delhi within the prescribed period, he shall, in addition to`
  line `the payment of tax, if any, be liable to a penalty not exceeding two and a half times the tax that would`
  line `have been payable had the goods been sold inside Delhi or one thousand rupees, whichever is more.`
  line
  line `(4) At every check-post or barrier, or at any other place when so required by an officer empowered by`
  line `the Administrator in this behalf, the driver or any other person in charge of a goods vehicle shall stop the`
  line `vehicle and keep it stationary so long as may be required by the officer in charge of the check-post or`
  line `barrier or the officer empowered as aforesaid to search the goods vehicle or part thereof, examine the`
  line `contents therein and inspect all records relating to the goods carried, which are in the possession of such`
  line `driver or other person in charge, who shall, if so required, give his name and address and the name and`
  line `address of the owner of the vehicle as well as those of the consignor and consignee of the goods.`
  line
  line `(5) If on an examination of the contents in a goods vehicle or the inspection of records relating to the`
  line `goods carried, any officer empowered by the Administrator in this behalf has reason to believe that the`
  line `owner or person in charge of such goods vehicle is attempting to evade payment of the tax due under this`
  line `Act, he may, for reasons to be recorded in writing and after hearing the owner or person in charge of the`
  line `goods vehicle, detain the goods and the goods so detained shall not be allowed to be transported unless`
  line `the owner, or his agent or the person in charge of the goods vehicle furnishes to the satisfaction of such`
  line `officer security in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed for an amount not exceeding one`
  line `thousand rupees or the amount of tax payable if such goods were sold in Delhi, whichever is more.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the security required to be furnished under sub-section (5) is not furnished within the`
  line `prescribed period such goods shall be disposed of in such manner and subject to such conditions as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "goods vehicle" shall include a motor vehicle, vessel,`
  line `boat, animal and any other form of conveyance.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (33175)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Publication of names, etc., of dealers whose certificates of registration are cancelled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33175&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Commissioner shall, at intervals not exceeding three months, publish in the Official Gazette such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed of dealers whose certificates of registration are cancelled under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (33176)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title Exemptions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33176&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Administrator is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public`
  line `interest so to do, he may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, exempt, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, and subject to such conditions, if any, as he may impose, any specified class of`
  line `sales by any specified class of dealers from payment of the whole or any part of the tax payable under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) If in respect of any sales which are exempt from payment of tax under sub-section (1), a breach of`
  line `any of the conditions subject to which such exemption was granted, is committed, the dealer responsible`
  line `for such breach shall be liable to pay tax in respect of all such sales as if no such exemption had been`
  line granted.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (33177)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Bar of suits in civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33177&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be brought in any civil court to set aside or modify`
  line `any assessment made or any order passed under this Act or the rules made thereunder and no prosecution,`
  line `suit or other proceeding shall lie against the Government or any officer of the Government for anything in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (33178)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Transfers during pendency of proceedings void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33178&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Where, during the pendency of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act, any person creates a charge on or parts with the possession by way of sale,`
  line `mortgage, gift or exchange or any other mode of transfer whatsoever, of any of his assets in favour of`
  line `any other person, such charge or transfer shall be void as against any claim in respect of any tax or`
  line `any other sum payable by such person as a result of the completion of the said proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (33179)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, not to apply to certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33179&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall`
  line `apply to--`
  line
  line `(i) any offence punishable under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other offence which under the provisions of that Code, may be tried along with such`
  line offence,
  line
  line `and every offence referred to in clause (i) or clause (ii) may be taken cognizance of by the court having`
  line `jurisdiction under this Act as if the provisions of that Chapter were not enacted.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (33180)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Application of the provisions of the Delhi Land Reforms Act, 1954 for purposes of recovery of sales tax recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33180&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of recovery of any amount`
  line `recoverable as arrears of land revenue under this Act, the provisions of the Delhi Land Reforms`
  line `Act, 1954 (Delhi Act 8 of 1954), as to recovery of arrears of land revenue shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in that Act or in any other enactment, be deemed to be in force throughout Delhi and the`
  line `provisions of the Revenue Recovery Act, 1890 (1 of 1890), shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (33181)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33181&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may make rules for carrying out the purposes of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the further period after the date of expiry of three consecutive years referred to`
  line `in sub-section (3) of section 3 for which liability to pay tax of a dealer shall continue;`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars to be contained in a declaration under sub-clause (v) of clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 4, or under section 5, as the case may be, the form of such declaration,`
  line `the authority from whom such forms shall be obtainable and the manner in which and the time within`
  line `which such declaration is to be furnished.`
  line
  line `(c) the period of turnover, the manner in which the turnover in relation to sale of any goods under`
  line `this Act shall be determined and the sales turnover which may be deducted under sub-clause (vi) of`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the restrictions and conditions subject to which the Commissioner may delegate his powers`
  line `under section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the authority to whom applications for registration under sections 14, 15, 16 and 17 may be`
  line `made and the form of such applications and the fees payable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure for and other matters incidental to registration of dealers, the granting of`
  line `certificates of registration, the period within which such certificates shall be granted and the forms of`
  line `such certificates;`
  line
  line `(g) the intervals at which, and the manner in which, the tax under this Act shall be payable under`
  line `section 21;`
  line
  line `(h) the returns to be furnished under sub-section (2) of section 21 and dates by which, and the`
  line `authority to whom, such returns shall be furnished;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure to be followed for assessment under section 23;`
  line
  line `(j) the circumstances in which, and the conditions subject to which, a dealer may be permitted to`
  line `pay a lump sum by way of composition under section 29 and the manner of determining such sum;`
  line
  line `(k) the form in which claims for refund or set-off may be preferred, the manner in which such`
  line `claims for refund shall be verified and the refunds or set-off under this Act shall be allowed;`
  line
  line `(l) the authority to whom information shall be furnished under section 40;`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions under which the production of accounts or documents or the furnishing of`
  line `information may be required under sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(n) the form and manner in which, and the authority to whom, appeals against assessment may be`
  line `filed under section 43, the manner in which such appeals shall be verified and the fees payable in`
  line `respect thereof and the procedure, to be followed by such authority;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner in which applications for revision under section 47 or for review`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 48 may be filed and the fee payable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(p) the conditions subject to which the Commissioner may authorise the persons appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9 to assist him to investigate offences under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 53;`
  line
  line `(q) the conditions under which offences may be compounded under section 54;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner in which, and the time within which, applications shall be made (including fees`
  line `payable in respect thereof), information furnished, securities given and notices served under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rules made under this Act may provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and in the case of a continuing contravention, with an`
  line `additional fine which may extend to twenty-five rupees for every day during which such contravention`
  line `continues after conviction for the first such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (33182)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33182&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (33183)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33183&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bengal Finance (Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as`
  line `in force in Delhi (hereinafter referred to as the said Act), is hereby repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such repeal shall not affect the previous operation of the said Act or any right, title,`
  line `obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred thereunder and subject thereto, anything done`
  line `or any action taken including any appointment, notification, notice, order, rule, form or certificate in the`
  line `exercise of any power conferred by or under the said Act shall be deemed to have been done or taken in`
  line `the exercise of the powers conferred by or under this Act, as if this Act were in force on the date on which`
  line `such thing was done or action was taken, and all arrears of tax and other amounts due at the`
  line `commencement of this Act may be recovered as if they had accrued under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any application for revision pending immediately before the date on which the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `is constituted under section 13 (hereafter in this section referred to as the notified date), before the`
  line `Commissioner under the Bengal Finance (Sales Tax) Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as in force in`
  line `the Union territory of Delhi shall on such date stand transferred to, and be disposed of by the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for revision shall be transferred to the Appellate Tribunal if the petitioner`
  line `making the application for revision waives his right of appeal to the Tribunal within fifteen days after the`
  line `notified date, in which case the application for revision shall be disposed of by the Commissioner as if it`
  line `were an application for revision made under section 47.`
  line
  line `(3) Any application for revision, pending immediately before the notified date, before the`
  line `Commissioner and transferred to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (2) shall be disposed of by the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal made to the Tribunal under and in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 43 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal against an order passed by an officer under this Act lies to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal after the notified date, and the period of limitation specified for filing such appeal under this Act`
  line `has not expired, then, such appeal shall lie to the Tribunal within thirty days of the notified date or within`
  line `the expiry of the period of limitation specified for filing such appeal, whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (33184)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33184&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficultly arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `the removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of one year from the commencement of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (33185)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024&sectionId=33185&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00015_197543_1517807320024
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where a dealer liable to pay tax under the Bengal Finance (Sales Tax)`
  line `Act, 1941 (Bengal Act VI of 1941), as in force in Delhi immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act is not liable to pay tax under the provisions of this Act, he shall, notwithstanding the repeal of the`
  line `first mentioned Act, continue to be liable to pay tax on the sales made by him after such commencement`
  line `of all goods--`
  line
  line `(i) purchased by him before such commencement,`
  line
  line `(ii) manufactured by him before or after such commencement out of raw materials purchased`
  line `before such commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
